{{Babi texts and scriptures}}
The '''''Arabic Bayán''''' is a book written by the [[Báb]] around 1848. Its larger sister book is the ''[[Persian Bayán]]''. The work is incomplete, containing only eleven [[Vahid]]s. Each Vahid serves as a chapter and contains nineteen [[Abwab]]. The grammar is highly irregular.{{Elaboration needed|date=December 2016}} The work was composed while the Báb was imprisoned in [[Maku, Iran]].
