In  [[Religion in ancient Rome|ancient Roman religion]] and [[Roman mythology|myth]], '''Nerio''' was an ancient war goddess and the personification of [[Courage|valor]]. She was the partner of [[Mars (mythology)|Mars]] in ancient cult practices, and was sometimes identified with the goddess [[Bellona (goddess)|Bellona]], and occasionally with the goddess [[Minerva]]. Spoils taken from enemies were sometimes dedicated to Nerio by the Romans. Nerio was later supplanted by mythologized deities appropriated and adapted from other religions.<ref>Grimal, p. 308.</ref>

